rComments: Great teacher, really funny. Gives plenty of examples and interesting stories.
Very kind man. He is obviously teaching about his passion.
Such a nice and interesting man. He was very insightful and extremely caring of how his students were doing in class-granted it was a cmall class but he was amazing to learn from!

I took many classes with this prof and for good reason. He made University worthwhile. If I could have changed my major and followed in his foot steps I would have. Not only a prof but a very dear person who cares deeply about the lives of people and his students. WELL WORTH MEETING AND LEARNING FROM HIM, YOU WILL LEARN ALOT AND APPRECIATE LIFE.

I took his class 5 years ago and i still remember it fondly. He's a great prof. Patient & enthusiastic. His class is an exciting & fun introduction to a subject that some people make very dry. He inspired me to change my degree and major in Anthropology. I'm so glad I did - thanks professor Darosa!
His enthusiasm is contagious. Tests are VERY predictable. Shows many interesting videos, and reading is very easy.
Fantastic prof!!!   cannot ask for any better or more passionate than him!!  preps you well for tests and exams, and marks fairly!
Go there.  He loves you already!
Brilliant professor, funny and smart. It's a joy to attend lectures, lots of films. Impossible not to fall in love with anthropology. Really easygoing and no final exam!
How can you not love his class?  This guy is literally in love with Anthropology and it is contageous!!
He's a great teacher and makes you want to learn
Extremely helpful - he really cares. Tends to ramble though...
